text: The 2010 South Australian state election was held on 20 March 2010 to elect the 52nd Parliament of South Australia, including all 47 seats in the House of Assembly and 11 of the 22 seats in the Legislative Council. It was conducted by the Electoral Commission of South Australia (ECSA). The incumbent Labor government, led by Premier Mike Rann, won a third term in government. They were opposed by the Liberal Party, led by Isobel Redmond. ==References== Category:2010 elections in Australia Category:Elections in South Australia Category:2010s in South Australia Category:March 2010 events
